How to record "login test" in JMeter
=========================

Step 1:  add "blazemeter" plugin to chrome browser

Step 2:  open browser and type your "login url" in address bar

Step 3: open "blazemeter" --> set record name as "Login_Test" --> click on record "run" button

Step 4. in login page, type "username" and "password" and click on "login" button

Step 5: in "blazemeter" --> click on record "stop" button and Export  .jmx file

Step 6: open "JMeter" Application and click on "Test Plan" ---> File ---> Open ---> select .jmx file

Step 7: in "JMeter" Application add Listener (e.g. View Result Tree)

Step 8: in "JMeter" Application Run Test and view result

